{"lemma":"حَيَوانٌ","slug":"حَيَوانٌ","root":"ح.#.#","root_slug":"ح-_-_","root_link":"/words/roots/ح-_-_","pos":"N","pos_camel":"noun","paradigm":[],"frequency_in_corpus":0,"cross_references":{"qac":{"found":true,"lemma_key":"حَيَوان","root":"حيي","pos":"N","occurrence_count":1},"wiktextract":{"found":true,"entry_count":1,"pos_tags":["noun"],"has_etymology":true,"sense_count":3},"lanes":{"found":true,"entry_ids":["n9681"],"search_url":"https://lanelexicon.com/?s=%D8%AD%D9%8E%D9%8A%D9%8E%D9%88%D8%A7%D9%86%D9%8C"}},"translations":null,"definition":{"source":"wiktextract","senses":[{"pos":"noun","gloss":"animal, beast","examples":[{"text":"الحَيَوَانُ الْمُفْتَرِسُ يَعِيشُ فِي الْغَابَةِ.","english":"The predatory animal lives in the forest."}]},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"animals, living creatures","tags":["collective"]},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"verbal noun of حَيَّ (ḥayya): life; (especially) long, eternal life","tags":["archaic","form-of","noun-from-verb"],"examples":[{"text":"وَمَا هَٰذِهِ ٱلْحَيَاةُ ٱلدُّنْيَا إِلَّا لَهْوٌ وَلَعِبٌ وَإِنَّ ٱلدَّارَ ٱلْآخِرَةَ لَهِيَ ٱلْحَيَوَانُ لَوْ كَانُوا يَعْلَمُونَ","english":"And this worldly life is not but diversion and amusement. And indeed, the home of the Hereafter – that is the [eternal] life, if only they knew."}]}]},"etymology":{"source":"wiktextract","text":"Inherited from Proto-West Semitic *ḥayaw- (“animal”). Cognate with Hebrew חיה (ḥayyā), Classical Syriac ܚܝܘܬܐ (ḥaywəṯā) and Ugaritic 𐎈𐎆𐎉 (ḥwṭ). Synchronically, a verbal noun of حَيَّ (ḥayya, “to live”)."},"ipa":["/ħa.ja.waːn/"],"lanes_definition":{"source":"lanes","entries":[{"entry_id":"n9681","headword_ar":"حَيَوَانٌ","root":"HY: or HY and Hyw","body":[{"kind":"text","text":"an inf. n. of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"HayiYa","text_ar":"حَيِىَ"},{"kind":"text","text":", like"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"HayaApN","text_ar":"حَيَاةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (IB,) but having an intensive signification: (Msb:) see"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"HayaApN","text_ar":"حَيَاةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", in two places. ―         -b2-  See also"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"HaY~N","text_ar":"حَىٌّ"},{"kind":"text","text":", first sentence. ―         -b3-  Also"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Any thing,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"things, possessing animal life,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Msb, K, *) whether"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"rational"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"irrational;"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"an animal,"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"animals;"},{"kind":"text","text":"] used alike as sing. and pl., because originally an inf. n.; (Msb;)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"contr. of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"mawataAnN","text_ar":"مَوَتَانٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"[q. v.]. (S.) ["},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"HayawaAnaAtN","text_ar":"حَيَوَانَاتٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"is used as its pl. of pauc. And hence,]"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AlHayawaAnaAtu","text_ar":"الحَيَوَانَاتُ"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Alxamosu","text_ar":"الخَمْسُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"The five animals"},{"kind":"text","text":"] is applied to what may be killed by a person in the state of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A_iHoraAm","text_ar":"اـِحْرَام"},{"kind":"text","text":", and by one engaged in prayer: (Msb in art."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"fsq","text_ar":"فسق"},{"kind":"text","text":":) these are"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the rat,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"mouse, and the biting dog, and"},{"kind":"text","text":"either"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the serpent, the crow termed"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^aboqaE","text_ar":"اَبْقَع"},{"kind":"text","text":","},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"and the kite,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the serpent, the scorpion, and the kite,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the serpent, the scorpion, and the crow,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the scorpion, the crow, and the kite."},{"kind":"text","text":"(Es-Suyootee, in “ El-Jámi' es-Sagheer, ” voce"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"xamosN","text_ar":"خَمْسٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":".) It is originally"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"HayayaAnN","text_ar":"حَيَيَانٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; (Sb, K, TA;) the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Y","text_ar":"ى"},{"kind":"text","text":"which is the final radical letter being changed into"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"w","text_ar":"و"},{"kind":"text","text":"because the occurrence of two"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Y","text_ar":"ى"},{"kind":"text","text":"together is disliked: (Sb, TA:) Aboo-'Othmán [El-Má- zinee] holds the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"w","text_ar":"و"},{"kind":"text","text":"to be a radical letter; but his opinion is said to be not admissible, because it is asserted that there is no instance in the language of a word of which the medial radical is"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Y","text_ar":"ى"},{"kind":"text","text":", and the final"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"w","text_ar":"و"},{"kind":"text","text":". (TA.)"}],"source_refs":["IB","Msb","Sb","TA"]}]},"classical_definitions":null}